CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 20, 1957, pg. A2, reads: "Back NAACP 100 Per Cent - The Rev. Charles H. Foggie, president of the Pittsburgh branch of the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People congratulated John B. Patterson, NAACP solicitor for Owl Cab Company. Mr. Patterson reported 100 per cent membership for regular Owl Cab drivers and the office force, totaling 70 members."
TitMainTitle: John B. Patterson and Pittsburgh branch NAACP president Charles H. Foggie during NAACP membership campaign
